  "response": "Cloudy urine can be caused by several factors:\n\n1. Mild causes:\n- Dehydration\n- High protein diet\n- Urinary tract infection (UTI)\n- Kidney stones\n- Sexually transmitted infections\n- Vaginal discharge\n- Prostate inflammation\n\n2. More serious potential causes:\n- Diabetes\n- Kidney disease\n- Liver problems\n- Certain medications\n- Presence of white blood cells or bacteria\n\n3. When to see a doctor:\n- Persistent cloudiness\n- Accompanied by pain\n- Blood in urine\n- Fever\n- Frequent urination\n- Unexplained weight loss\n\nIt's important to note that occasional cloudy urine isn't always a sign of serious illness, but if it persists or is accompanied by other symptoms, you should consult a healthcare professional for proper diagnosis and treatment.\n\nWould you like me to elaborate on any of these points?",
